      <section eId="sec_CHC-774">
        <num>CHC 774</num>
        <heading>774. Â Physical and mental examination for disposition</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-774__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Following the adjudication, the court may order such physical and mental examination and evaluation of any child of the family and his caretaker as may be helpful in determining a fair and just disposition.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-774__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>After giving the caretaker a reasonable opportunity to be heard, the court may order that he shall contribute to the cost of any court-ordered examination or evaluation in an amount commensurate with his ability to pay.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=73365</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
